### 1.1.1.1.2 Calculating For A Point And A Line

To determine if a point lies on a line, substitute the point into the vector equation of the line and solve for a unique value of \(\lambda\)

If a unique solution is found, the point lies on the line.

If not, it does not lie on the line.

To find foot of perpendicular \(\overline{\mathbf{O}F}\) from Point A to line \(l\) :

Let F be foot of perpendicular from point to line

Since F lies on \(l\), let \(\overline{\mathbf{O}F}\) = vector equation of line

Since \(\overline{\mathbf{A}F}\perp l\), let \(\overline{\mathbf{A}F}\cdot\mathbf{b}=\mathbf{0}\) to find value of \(\lambda\)

Sub back value of \(\lambda\) into \(l\) to find \(\overline{\mathbf{O}F}\)

